# Aleria V2 — Architecture Rules

## Stack
- Next.js 16 (App Router, Turbopack, SSG)
- React 19, TypeScript 5, Tailwind CSS v4
- Framer Motion for animations
- Lucide React for icons
- Deployment: Vercel

## File rules
- Max 150 lines per file. Split if larger.
- No barrel exports (index.ts re-exports). Import directly.
- No unused imports, variables, or files. Run `npm run lint` before finishing.

## Styling
- All colors and radii come from CSS custom properties in `globals.css`.
- Use Tailwind utilities that reference these tokens (`text-foreground`, `bg-muted`, `border-border/30`).
- Never hardcode color values (no `#fff`, `rgb()`, `oklch()` inline in components).
- Use opacity modifiers on tokens for subtle variants: `text-muted-foreground/70`, `border-border/15`.

## Components

### Marketing primitives (`components/marketing/`)
These are the building blocks for all marketing pages:
- `Btn` — Polymorphic button/link. Use `href` for links, omit for buttons.
- `Section` — Section wrapper. Use `background`, `spacing`, `divider` props.
- `Container` — Max-width wrapper. Use `size` prop.
- `Badge` — Section label. Just text, no borders/pills.
- `LinkArrow` — Text link with animated arrow icon.
- `MediaFrame` — Placeholder for video/image content.
- `Metrics` — Display key numbers inline.

### Sections (`components/sections/{page}/`)
- One file per section, named by content (e.g., `hero.tsx`, `sources.tsx`).
- Each section receives `{ className?: string }` via `SectionProps`.
- Use `Section` + `Container` wrappers, not raw `<section>` + `<div>`.

### Layout (`components/layout/`)
- `header.tsx`, `footer.tsx`, `mobile-nav.tsx`
- Use `Btn` from marketing, not Shadcn Button.

## Animations
- Use Framer Motion `motion.div` with `whileInView` for scroll-triggered animations.
- Consistent ease: `[0.4, 0, 0.2, 1]`
- Consistent duration: `0.5` (standard), `0.6` (hero/cta)
- Always `viewport={{ once: true, margin: "-80px" }}`
- Use `variants` + `staggerChildren` for lists, not individual `delay` values.

## What NOT to do
- Do NOT import from `@/components/ui/` on marketing pages (that directory is reserved for future app UI).
- Do NOT use Shadcn components on marketing pages.
- Do NOT add icon-in-a-box patterns (bordered square with icon inside). Use typography and whitespace.
- Do NOT add `"use client"` unless the component uses hooks or event handlers.
- Do NOT create hooks or utilities unless they're used by 2+ files.

## Configuration
- Site config (nav, URLs, metadata): `config/site.ts`
- Fonts: `lib/fonts.ts`
- CSS tokens: `app/globals.css`
- Types: `types/index.ts`
